This product contains constexpr transcriptions of third-party hash and digest
algorithms. The transcriptions are original code, but they closely follow
their reference implementations; the upstream notices are reproduced below in
two classes.

Applicability: every entry below applies only to distributions that actually
contain the referenced files - i.e. that build/link the named Bazel rule
(directly or transitively). A binary or source distribution that does not
include //mbo/hash:hash_extra_cc carries none of the compliance entries and
may omit them; the courtesy entries impose no obligation either way. When in
doubt, ship this NOTICE file as a whole - reproducing an inapplicable notice
is harmless, omitting an applicable one is not.

1. License compliance - required by the upstream license because the licensed
   reference implementation effectively is the specification and the
   transcription follows its expression:
   - rapidhash (MIT): mbo/hash/hash_rapidhash.h
   - xxHash / XXH64 / XXH3 (BSD-2-Clause): mbo/hash/hash_xxh64.h and
     mbo/hash/hash_xxh3.h
   Both ship exclusively in the opt-in Bazel rule //mbo/hash:hash_extra_cc
   (header mbo/hash/hash_extra.h): these notices apply if and only if that
   rule's code is included - directly or transitively. The default
   //mbo/hash:hash_cc (header mbo/hash/hash.h, incl. the default mumbo/jumbo
   algorithms) contains no notice-bearing code, so distributions built
   without hash_extra_cc carry no third-party notice obligations from this
   repository at all.

2. Courtesy attribution - public-domain/CC0 upstreams with no notice
   obligation, recorded for provenance:
   - MurmurHash3, SipHash, FNV-1a: in //mbo/hash:hash_cc
   - BLAKE3 (CC0-1.0 OR Apache-2.0; CC0 elected): mbo/digest/digest_blake3.h
     in //mbo/digest:digest_cc

Algorithms implemented from public standards (FIPS 180-4, FIPS 202, RFC 1321,
RFC 2104, RFC 7693) are original code and carry no upstream notices. See the
"Third-party components" section of README.md for the full reference list.

